---
Sorcerers are multi-school arcane casters who inherit the Chromatic Circle tradition of elemental synthesis.
The Circle rejected single-school specialization, holding that the deepest power lies in combining multiple elements.
The Confluence Texts document observed interactions between spell schools organized by interaction type: resonance, interference, amplification, cancellation.
Combat role is offensive caster deploying multiple elemental schools simultaneously to overwhelm specialized defenses.
When academic consolidation outlawed most Circle branches, the tradition survived in small apprentice chains.
Each chain preserved the Confluence Text portions most relevant to its specialization.
Key combat doctrine: an opponent with defenses optimized against one element is vulnerable to simultaneous multi-element engagement.
Sorcerers command breadth and synthesis. Wizards command exactitude and sequence.
The Grand Magi class synthesizes the Sorcerer (Chromatic Circle) and Wizard (Axiomatic Schools) approaches.
